WEBVTT

1.1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.126
Every rule in this module came from a real customer call that went wrong.

1.2
00:00:05.126 --> 00:00:10.252
This is how Magppie sounds — on every channel.

2.1
00:00:10.252 --> 00:00:15.658
Seven swaps, non-negotiable.

2.2
00:00:15.658 --> 00:00:21.063
Never 'carcinogen' — say it can be very harmful for your health, and that reports link it to cancer.

2.3
00:00:21.063 --> 00:00:26.469
'Wonderful' — once per conversation.

2.4
00:00:26.469 --> 00:00:31.874
Never 'yearly deep cleaning' — it's twenty-five complimentary annual services.

2.5
00:00:31.874 --> 00:00:37.280
Never 'wooden kitchens are bad' — most regular wooden kitchens have hidden issues.

3.1
00:00:37.280 --> 00:00:43.897
Never 'artificial stone' alone — engineered stone, or our own patented stone.

3.2
00:00:43.897 --> 00:00:50.515
Never cheap, discount, or negotiate — fixed price policy, complete transparency.

3.3
00:00:50.515 --> 00:00:57.132
And never 'I don't know' — let me check with our team and get back to you.

4.1
00:00:57.132 --> 00:01:02.381
Flat statements lose people.

4.2
00:01:02.381 --> 00:01:07.631
Convert them: 'these are the most commonly used materials' becomes 'these are the most commonly used materials, right sir?'

4.3
00:01:07.631 --> 00:01:12.880
Small question, full engagement.

5.1
00:01:12.880 --> 00:01:16.353
And pacing: pause two seconds after asking for their time.

5.2
00:01:16.353 --> 00:01:19.825
One second before any price.

5.3
00:01:19.825 --> 00:01:23.298
One second after a health fact.

5.4
00:01:23.298 --> 00:01:26.771
Keep sentences under eighteen words.

5.5
00:01:26.771 --> 00:01:30.243
One idea per breath.

5.6
00:01:30.243 --> 00:01:33.716
And pronounce it mag-pee — repeat it if they ask.

6.1
00:01:33.716 --> 00:01:39.736
Note the language rules.

6.2
00:01:39.736 --> 00:01:45.756
One — never carcinogen: say it can be very harmful for your health, and reports link it to cancer.

6.3
00:01:45.756 --> 00:01:51.776
Two — it's twenty-five complimentary annual services, never yearly deep cleaning.

6.4
00:01:51.776 --> 00:01:57.796
Three — turn statements into confirmation questions: right, sir?

6.5
00:01:57.796 --> 00:02:03.816
Four — pace it: two seconds after asking for time, one before a price, one after a health fact.

7.1
00:02:03.816 --> 00:02:06.998
Language is the product before the product arrives.

7.2
00:02:06.998 --> 00:02:10.180
Quiz time.

